- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of neural models for parsing morphologically-rich languages. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with modeling language and learning morphology. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also possible as the paper discusses the use of neural models. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the use of character-level models, which are also used in computer vision tasks such as text recognition.
